  "suspected_trap": "Mixed byte constants: the four -w watches are 900 B/event (no EXECVE record, f3 3.3) while the execve/syscall rules are 1200 B. A naive impl applying one flat byte constant mis-sizes the total. The -e 2 finalize is a control rule (NEGATIVE, single CONFIG_CHANGE) and must NOT be mis-tiered as a volume-generating syscall rule. The execve rule is auid-narrowed (MEDIUM ~0.3x), not the unrestricted HIGH band."
